&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Director of Learning Design for Language Learning, you will set the pedagogical vision and execution strategy for Duolingo’s&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;language-learning experiences — driving learning impact, curriculum quality, and innovation at global scale. You’ll lead a team of multi-disciplinary learning designers, and partner with product leadership to ship delightful, effective learning in the Duolingo style. This job is based in Pittsburgh.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🧠 You will...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ship effective learning at scale:&lt;/strong&gt; partner with Product, Design, and Engineering to translate pedagogy into fun and motivating in‑app experiences that build listening, speaking, reading, and writing skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead and develop a world‑class team&lt;/strong&gt; of learning designers, leveling up their craft, velocity, and effectiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive an experiment‑led practice:&lt;/strong&gt; help design outcome‑focused A/B tests, align on success metrics (e.g., CEFR-aligned progress, retention, speaking/writing gains), and assist with analyzing learning and engagement impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Establish content quality systems&lt;/strong&gt; (guidelines, rubrics, review workflows) that ensure linguistic accuracy, difficulty calibration, and a high-quality bar across language courses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead through example by &lt;strong&gt;using AI &lt;/strong&gt;to improve your craft, and encouraging your team to do the same&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Explore the future of language teaching:&lt;/strong&gt; develop and validate roadmaps for new skills, modes, and curricula that extend Duolingo’s impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;✅ You have...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Depth in language learning design&lt;/strong&gt;: extensive experience (typically 10+ years) designing language curricula or consumer learning products, with proven impact at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;People leadership&lt;/strong&gt;: 5+ years leading multi‑disciplinary teams; experience managing managers and establishing high‑bar standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product sense&lt;/strong&gt;: an instinct for creating simple, delightful, and intuitive user experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational rigor&lt;/strong&gt;: proficiency in large-scale content operations, QA processes, and tooling to maintain quality across many languages, ideally including experience with human‑in‑the‑loop AI workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outstanding communication&lt;/strong&gt;: clear, kind, and persuasive across audiences, including executive and cross‑functional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;⭐ Exceptional candidates will have...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Graduate degree in Applied Linguistics, Second Language Acquisition, TESOL, Linguistics, Learning Science, Cognitive Science, HCI, or a relevant language field; familiarity with proficiency frameworks (e.g., CEFR, ACTFL) and assessment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of partnering with product, design, and engineering to ship lovable, effective features on mobile&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
